ndencies**\\n\\nI need to figure out if the boot artifact includes servlet environment without the dependencies. It seems like building only with Spring Boot might pull optional ones. I should inspect the dependency tree, maybe through the POM or local Gradle. I can add test dependencies, but they might need to stay within the target test source root. There’s a lot to consider about converting ApplicationEnvironment to a ConfigurableEnvironment type. I think I can create a custom ApplicationContextFactory for testing purposes too. It's a bit of a puzzle!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Defining test structure for Spring**\\n\\nI’m trying to understand how Spring context might wrap and ensure I set a one-to-one mapping from my dynamic-access class to the test file. It looks like I need to create an `EnvironmentConverterTest.java`, keeping it outside the `org.springframework.boot` package, which is crucial. I'll consider making it a top-level public test class, since inner classes might generate unexpected file names with the `$` character. It’s all about adhering to the public API rules! I should also check if the `ApplicationContextFactory` has any functional interface features.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating environment type overrides**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to override `getEnvironmentType` and create an anonymous class for the test. Although, naming it a test class might not be ideal. It seems like a dynamic-access one-to-one mapping could work, especially if I use a `private static final class StandardEnvironmentContextFactory`. Making it public should be fine, but do I need to import `AnnotationConfigApplicationContext`? The `spring-context` dependency should handle that transitively, so I might just proceed with `ConfigurableApplicationContext`. There are a lot of details to keep in mind!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gGhb0VGLeisgQYhmrENnF1Xo|fc_0bd5a8a2ad588708016a24c0120ea481969609aa7c0a91de83", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/EnvironmentConverterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework_boot.spring_boot;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.springframework.boot.ApplicationContextFactory;\nimport org.springframework.boot.Banner;\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringBootConfiguration;\nimport org.springframework.boot.WebApplicationType;\nimport org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.AnnotationConfigApplicationContext;\nimport org.springframework.core.env.ConfigurableEnvironment;\nimport org.springframework.core.env.StandardEnvironment;\n\npublic class EnvironmentConverterTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void runConvertsDefaultApplicationEnvironmentToFactoryEnvironmentType() {\n        SpringApplication application = new SpringApplication(TestApplication.class);\n        application.setApplicationContextFactory(new StandardEnvironmentContextFactory());\n        application.setBannerMode(Banner.Mode.OFF);\n        application.setLogStartupInfo(false);\n        application.setRegisterShutdownHook(false);\n        application.setWebApplicationType(WebApplicationType.NONE);\n        application.setAdditionalProfiles(\"converted\");\n\n        try (ConfigurableApplicationContext context = application.run(\"--sample.value=from-argument\")) {\n            ConfigurableEnvironment environment = context.getEnvironment();\n            assertThat(environment).isExactlyInstanceOf(StandardEnvironment.class);\n            assertThat(environment.getActiveProfiles()).containsExactly(\"converted\");\n            assertThat(environment.getProperty(\"sample.value\")).isEqualTo(\"from-argument\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class StandardEnvironmentContextFactory implements ApplicationContextFactory {\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<? extends ConfigurableEnvironment> getEnvironmentType(WebApplicationType webApplicationType) {\n            return StandardEnvironment.class;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ConfigurableApplicationContext create(WebApplicationType webApplicationType) {\n            return new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext();\n        }\n\n    }\n\n    @SpringBootConfiguration(proxyBeanMethods = false)\n    public static class TestApplication {\n\n    }\n\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1183, "output": 1399, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28694, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780793337280, "responseId": "resp_0bd5a8a2ad588708016a24bff9cbbc819682ad0ecb053f230a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_gGhb0VGLeisgQYhmrENnF1Xo|fc_0bd5a8a2ad588708016a24c0120ea481969609aa7c0a91de83", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2506 bytes to tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/EnvironmentConverterTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780793368353}]}
