tionContextFactory` whose expected environment type is `StandardEnvironment`. This forces Spring Boot to convert the default application environment, reaching:\n\n- `Class#getDeclaredConstructor(...)`\n- `Constructor#newInstance(...)`\n\nIt also verifies the converted environment preserves active profiles and command-line property sources.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0bd5a8a2ad588708016a24c02c7d6c8196ab2c2d707d79be39\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 386, "output": 465, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29523, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780793378801, "responseId": "resp_0bd5a8a2ad588708016a24c0234a7481969ca156362ef47226"}, "toolResults": []}
